You watch as the mouse soul you've placed on the statue floats peacefully into the stone.
The stone begins to crack and lift away into an inpenetrable cloud of grey dust, waving your arms exposes the grey body of a mouse exactly the same size and shame except now
there seems the be the slightest rise and fall on its still granite belly,
Could it really be breathing? You want to touch it....
endmsg
